snippet.textDisplay:
I think the glass doors are cool, although, definitely consider larger entrances for each studio that will need equipment put in it. Otherwise your Combo Rollers w/ the Skypanels and Sachtler Heads will have to be folded up before you can move it in and out, which could be very time consuming for the GnE and Camera crew.

For the cyc idea - I think it's awesome for you to have a cyc space with a top down soft box or even Quasar/Astera grid. The only concern is that the room you have in mind putting that feels a bit too small. Additionally for your top-down stuff you will likely need to remove your overhead lighting that is currently installed to allow for for the perma build to be on the same height (if not higher) as otherwise you may run into issues where the lighting is too close to your subject (Assuming you will be putting relatively bigger subjects in that space).

Possibly a camera prep floor? Your Camera teams would love that and will find it very useful: having a dedicated area with lens and color charts, prep tables and camera tools to test, calibrate, repair and prepare camera equipment in house is invaluable asset. We have it in-house and everybody loves it.

GnE wise - consider a powerful distro - not just 20amp breakers. Something along the lines of a 60AMP Bates, or even 100AMP Camlock would be amazing. What it will allow you to do is bring big lights to the studio for those shows you are producing, which require just this extra bit of electricity, without the need of renting another studio, or renting a big generator. One example would be - say you wanna use the natural daylight from the windows - to counter it you may need some large lighting source for your fill (say Skypanel 360, Arri M40, or Arrisun 2.5k) - a more powerful distro would allow you to do that.

For your ceiling lighting in the main area, since you have such a nice polished concrete, i recommend a small scissor lift. It will make every lighting technician's job so much faster and efficient.

Great stuff though! I got a little studio space of my own about 6 months ago and me and we had a massive improvement of the content we've been producing because of it, so I am excited to see the new visual upgrades coming up from you :)
